annotationA: Serum response factor homolog; Required for the formation of intervein tissue of the wing. Acts in a dosage-dependent manner to suppress wing vein formation and promote development of intervein cells. Might play a role in the proper formation and maintenance of the trachea
annotationB: Myogenic-determination protein; Nautilus (Nau) belongs to the bHLH family of transcription factors. It is the unique Drosophila ortholog of the mammalian family of bHLH Myogenic Regulatory Factors. Nau is involved in somatic muscle myogenesis
